For details on mass rebuild see https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/Fedora_26_Mass_Rebuild
This bug appears to have been reported against 'rawhide' during the Fedora 26 development cycle. Changing version to '26'.

Created attachment 1288390 Remove flex patch, no longer needed
The flex patch is no longer needed with Fedora 26, and it is now causing builds to fail. I am attaching a patch to remove it. It might be possible to adjust the patch so it works with older versions of Fedora, but looking at how often this package is updated, I figured that wasn't really needed. This is a blocker for some projects. If this isn't fixed withing two weeks, we will have a proven packager merge this patch in and build it.
